  "prompt": "What is Roadrunner Technical Support?",
  "response": "Roadrunner Technical Support typically refers to the customer service and assistance offered for users of Roadrunner email, a service that was originally provided by Time Warner Cable, which later became Spectrum after a merger with Charter Communications.\n\nRoadrunner Technical Support helps users troubleshoot common issues such as:\n- Email login problems\n- Password recovery or reset\n- Configuration of email settings on various devices (computers, smartphones, tablets)\n- Issues with sending or receiving emails\n- Spam and security concerns\n\nCustomers can usually reach Roadrunner Technical Support through various channels such as phone, online chat, or by visiting the support section on the Spectrum website where comprehensive guides and FAQs are available.\n\nIf you are experiencing issues with Roadrunner email, it's a good idea to consult the official support resources provided by Spectrum to get the most accurate and up-to-date assistance.",
